// *** Banters with Yoshimo (index 17000...17499) ***
@17000 = ~Afaaq, you are obviously not from around here.  Do you care to tell me where you hail from?~
@17001 = ~My home lies far beyond the material plane, out of reach for most mortals.  However, I have lived for quite some time in Calimshan, far to the south of here.~
@17002 = ~Ah, Calimshan.  A very rich country from what I've heard. It is also a place where you can meet all kinds of people and other races.~
@17003 = ~That is correct. Calimshan has always been a very rich nation and a melting pot of many different cultures.  Although its splendor pales in comparison to the wonders of the ancient Calim Empire.~
@17004 = ~I had considered visiting that place for a time, but in the end I wound up in Athkatla instead.~
@17005 = ~It is a good place too. There are lots of opportunities for someone like me to make a good living.~
@17006 = ~You are far away from home as well.  Why did you leave it in the first place?~
@17007 = ~The answer is surprisingly simple.  There comes a time in the life of a man when he realizes that his home has become too small and confined. Instead of settling down and leading a strictly regulated life, he took the opportunity to see the world and meet interesting people.~
@17008 = ~I see.  And did you find what you were looking for?~
@17009 = ~But of course!  Cities like this are life's blood for someone of my profession. You can find your luck literally around every corner. If you have a quick wit and a winning smile, that is.~


