// *** Banters with Edwin (index 19500...19999) ***
@19500 = ~Haha, the lamp is finally mine.~
@19501 = ~You will be MY plaything when the spell takes effect, Afaaq.~
@19502 = ~No... it cannot be... Help me, <CHARNAME>!~
@19550 = ~It must be unbearable for a proud and noble djinn to be trapped in that prison, considering that you also have to suffer the indignity to follow every foolish whim of your masters. Don't you wish to escape this prison and enjoy freedom once more?~
@19551 = ~Your concern over my well-being is touching, wizard.~
@19552 = ~My current plight is just a temporary condition. I can allow myself to be patient, since time is of no real consequence for my kind.~
@19553 = ~But surely even your patience will snap eventually. The Red Wizards have considerable knowledge of enslaving creatures as well as breaking enslavements. I could be of great help to you in this matter.~
@19554 = ~I have no doubt about your willingness to help me. However, Red Wizards are not known for their generosity.~
@19555 = ~Well, of course I'm not doing it purely out of the goodness of my heart. All I desire is a small favor that should easily be within your power. What say you?~
@19556 = ~You are not the first wizard of your order I have the misfortune to deal with. But unlike your brothers in Thay you are especially easy to read.~
@19557 = ~My previous masters forced me to perform unimaginably cruel and hideous tasks. But they all were well aware of the consequences of their actions. I am not so sure in your case. I would rather suffer another millennium in their clutches than being bound to grant you even the smallest of favors imaginable.~
@19558 = ~(How dare you!) Ahem, you wound me deeply, Afaaq. Think about it some more. I'm sure you will see the advantages of my offer. (As do I for myself.)~
@19600 = ~Afaaq, please satisfy my curiosity. What was your life before your unfortunate encounters on the prime material plane?~
@19601 = ~I am certain that even the most insignificant tale from my past would vastly exceed your imagination, wizard.~
@19602 = ~Oh, do I hear a hint of sadness in your voice? Or is it regret? Your past must have been glorious indeed.~
@19603 = ~Our past is an important part of us. It shapes us and prepares for events that have not yet come to pass. Joy and sadness, anticipation and regret are all part of life. I would not have it otherwise.~
@19604 = ~I have noticed you are exceptionally reticent when it comes to your own past, wizard. Do you regret past decisions?~
@19605 = ~What nonsense! I have accomplished more than the ragtag party I'm pleasing with my presence would experience in a lifetime. My current endeavor will be just as fruitful in the end. (Even if those monkeys in Thay refuse to see it yet.)~
@19650 = ~Afaaq, I would have a word with you. Alone.~
@19651 = ~I am sure you would. Although my anticipation of this conversation is limited.~
@19652 = ~Silence! This is very important (to me).~
@19653 = ~Do you remember our first conversation? I promised to help you breaking the enchantment that keeps you chained to the lamp.~
@19654 = ~I know your kind appreciates gems, magical items or opulent meals. My family is quite affluent. I can provide you with wealth beyond your wildest dreams. All I desire is a small service of you in return. What is your decision?~
@19655 = ~You think yourself clever, but the desperation in your words is poorly veiled. Even if I did not have the experience of countless lifetimes of you mortals, I would be wary of your intent. Others of my race may be more tolerant in this regard, but I am not.~
@19656 = ~My service will never be available for your kind. I do not do this out of malice or selfishness, but rather to protect you and everyone else from the mistakes that will inevitably be the result of your actions. Do not ask me of it again.~
@19657 = ~So you refuse a helping hand and the opportunity to gain wealth beyond measure at the same time? You are more a fool than I expected. It is your loss, djinn. (But don't think I will give up so easily.)~
@19658 = ~So you refuse the opportunity to gain wealth beyond measure? You are more a fool than I expected. It is your loss, djinn.~
@19659 = ~In addition I can offer you riches beyond your dreams. My family is quite affluent. I know your kind appreciates gems, magical items or opulent meals. All I desire is a small service of you in return. What is your decision?~
@19700 = ~I can not believe the foolishness of that wizard. He should have known that artifacts like these are protected against half-hearted attempts to break their enchantments.~
@19701 = ~He could have easily imprisoned everyone including you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>, by his foolish actions. I hope you have a way to free him from his predicament, because he will not have the power to do it by himself anymore.~
@19702 = ~I guess he has learned his lesson now. Would a Freedom spell release him from his imprisonment?~
@19703 = ~I think he has learned his lesson now. How exactly can I release him from his predicament?~
@19704 = ~That fool is more trouble than he's worth it. Let him rot in hell, for all I care.~
@19705 = ~Yes, I think it would. But it has to be cast near the place of his imprisonment to be effective. I hope you have a spell like that ready.~
@19706 = ~Only a Freedom spell will release the wizard from his prison. But it has to be used near the place of his imprisonment to be effective. I hope you have a way to cast this spell.~
@19707 = ~I can not blame you if you want to leave him where he is. But if you change your mind, a Freedom spell will probably release him from his prison. It has to be cast near the place of his imprisonment to be effective, however.~
@19708 = ~Can't you grant me the wish to free Edwin from his state?~
@19709 = ~Yes, I can grant you a wish to release someone from imprisonment. However, I can do it only a single time. Please think carefully before you make use of my offer.~
@19750 = ~It is about time that you came to my rescue. I...I thought I had to waste one of my own spells to free myself. (How very clever of me.)~
@19751 = ~Do you still need my superior intellect, <CHARNAME>?~
@19752 = ~Of course. I'm sure you won't try anything stupid like that again.~
@19753 = ~Not at the moment. I will have to think about your careless actions for a while.~
@19754 = ~What?! After all you have done, Edwin? You should be lucky that I cared enough to free you from your predicament.~
@19755 = ~Fine, I didn't care for your presence anyway. Good riddance!~
@19756 = ~Not at the moment. I will have to think about your careless actions for a while. I'll send you back to the pocket plane.~
@19757 = ~Not at the moment. I will have to think about your careless actions for a while. Just wait here for a while.~


// *** Banters with Viconia (index 20000...20499) ***
@20000 = ~Afaaq, you are rather glum and submissive for a djinn. Has life broken you that much already?~
@20001 = ~The path of life does not always follow a straight line, just as air can be felt as a light breeze at one time or a violent storm at another. I am merely weathering it out like I did countless times before.~
@20002 = ~You are truly a disgrace to your kind, given that you have powers at your fingertips that would make every mortal green with envy.~
@20003 = ~My House had once put genies into service. Despite our best efforts we could never break their will nor abate their pride.~
@20004 = ~My House had once put genies into service. Despite our best efforts we could never break their will nor abate their pride. Obviously someone else was more successful with you.~
@20005 = ~False pride may cause more damage in the long term. You above all should know very well what I am talking about.~
@20006 = ~Pride allowed me to survive and made me stronger. If I had displayed such meek behavior at that time I would have shared the fate of everyone else of my House.~
@20007 = ~Pride allowed me to survive and made me stronger. If I had displayed such meek behavior at that time I would have shared the fate of everyone else of my House. You above all should know about Drow society.~
@20008 = ~Only time will tell if you made the right choice.~


// *** Banters with Korgan (index 20500...20999) ***
@20500 = ~Argh!  Stop it, I give up!~
@20501 = ~Show yerself, Afaaq!~
@20502 = ~Where are ye?~
@20503 = ~Don't hide, ye coward!~
@20504 = ~Come on, ye bloody bastard!~
@20505 = ~Argh, ye're gettin' on me nerves!~


// *** Djinni Lamp Only Dialog (index 21000...21499) ***
@21000 = ~(The magical lamp in your possession starts to emit a faint pulsating light and the djinni turns his attention to you.)~
@21001 = ~(However before you can react, the djinni turns away and the lamp is dark once again.)~
@21002 = ~I thank you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. You have rescued me again from those despicable rakshasa, and for that I am grateful. I doubt they will hunt me down anymore as you have killed the one who managed to bind me to the lamp.~
@21003 = ~Something does not feel right. I urge you to be very careful, my <PRO_LADYLORD>.~
@21004 = ~That is a terrible fate, to be tormented endlessly by the drow without hope of deliverance. If we were not on a mission of secrecy, I would gladly free the djinni from his bonds.~
@21005 = ~I thank you for risking your disguise and even your life to release the djinni from his bonds, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. Do not worry though, by destroying his physical shell he was able to return home without permanent damage.~
@21006 = ~My <PRO_LADYLORD>, I strongly advise you to keep my presence hidden while you explore the lower caves. Whatever has made its home down there will surely react with hostility to any djinni intrusion.~
@21007 = ~The lamp doesn't appear to work.~
@21008 = ~You hold the lamp in your hands and attempt to find out what's inside. But you are unable to see anything...~
@21009 = ~...except for a faintly glowing mist which you have no explanation for. After a while you put it back into your inventory.~
@21010 = ~You look into the lamp but find nothing of interest.~
@21011 = ~(Put the lamp away)~
@21012 = ~(Switch places with Afaaq)~
@21013 = ~(Force the djinni into the lamp)~
@21014 = ~You focus your thoughts on the djinni and everything around you becomes blurry...~
@21015 = ~You open the lamp and begin to focus your thoughts. After a few moments you feel a slight gust of wind. The djinni is in his lamp and you put it back into your inventory.~
@21016 = ~You open the lamp and begin to focus your thoughts. After a few moments you feel a slight gust of wind and hear a faint sigh.~
@21017 = ~The djinni is in his lamp and you put it back into your inventory. You feel a little guilty, however.~
@21018 = ~You open the lamp and begin to focus your thoughts. After a few moments you feel a slight gust of wind and hear a faint growl.~
@21019 = ~The djinni is in his lamp and you put it back into your inventory. You are certain that the djinni is annoyed by your actions, though.~
@21020 = ~You open the lamp and begin to focus your thoughts. After a few moments you feel a slight gust of wind and hear a faint scream.~
@21021 = ~The djinni is in his lamp and you put it back into your inventory.~

