@58283 = ~A-a pleasure to meet you.~
@58284 = ~The pleasure is all mine.~
@58285 = ~I greet you, Afaaq. A friend of <CHARNAME> is also a friend of mine.~
@58286 = ~I am honored by your words.~
@58287 = ~Well met, Afaaq. I look forward to fighting by your side.~
@58288 = ~Greetings, Mazzy. I hope your dream comes true someday.~
@58289 = ~Little sister is good. I'd rather see you as my little <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>, <CHARNAME>.~
@58290 = ~And you are our new travelling companion, Afaaq? You look like a cheerful fellow.~
@58291 = ~I am honored to make your acquaintance, Imoen.~
@58292 = ~You betcha! I'm sure we'll get on like a house on fire, hehe.~
@58293 = ~Ah, I am looking forward to your company, too.~
@58294 = ~If you are a friend of <CHARNAME>, I will come to terms with your company.~
@58295 = ~There is no need to fear me, Valygar. Neither by what I am nor who I am.~
@58296 = ~Nothing good will come from magic, in whatever form it will appear.~
@58297 = ~I respect your opinion, but you may see one day that your anger and fear are misdirected.~
@58298 = ~Oh, look Boo! He looks just like the one in the children's book Dynaheir used to read to us each evening.~
@58299 = ~Hello, genie in a bottle. I am Minsc and this is Boo.~
@58300 = ~I greet you, Minsc...and Boo? Who is Boo?~
@58301 = ~Boo is a miniature giant space hamster. And he is my friend.~
@58302 = ~A miniature giant...? Ah, I am pleased to make his acquaintance, too.~
@58303 = ~<CHARNAME>, you should know by now that I put no value to my heritage, as long as I can help the people in need.~
@58304 = ~I am pleased to make your acquaintance, Afaaq.~
@58305 = ~The pleasure is all mine. You are pursuing a laudable goal, my lady. A goal which is worth supporting.~
@58306 = ~Greetings to you. I am Anomen Delryn, a warrior priest of Helm.~
@58307 = ~I am pleased to make your acquaintance.~
@58308 = ~You are lucky that we came to your rescue, Afaaq.~
@58309 = ~If it weren't for my bravery, we wouldn't have entered the strange gate and you would still be in the possession of those demonic beasts.~
@58310 = ~Yes, of course. I am very grateful. <CHARNAME> will certainly appreciate all the good deeds you have accomplished, I am sure of it.~
@58311 = ~Greetings, Afaaq. I am pleased to make your acquaintance.~
@58312 = ~Is that all I am to you, <CHARNAME>? If I hadn't wasted my time with the Order, I would have been the greatest fighter in all of Amn.~
@58313 = ~And you are to travel with us for a while? I'm not sure how useful you will be, being chained to that magical lamp.~
@58314 = ~And you are to travel with us for a while? I'm not sure how useful you will be to us.~
@58315 = ~I greet you, Anomen. Whatever trouble you have, I am sure you will overcome it in time.~
@58316 = ~Well met, Afaaq. I'm glad to see our little party has grown again.~
@58317 = ~I am Yoshimo, a freelancer, adventurer and good friend of <CHARNAME>.~
@58318 = ~The pleasure is all mine, but it pains me to see yet another soul sharing a similar fate to my own.~
@58319 = ~You must be mistaken, my good friend. I'm enjoying my freedom more than anyone else.~
@58320 = ~Don't be shy to ask for help, if you're having trouble in dealing with my fellow townspeople. I'll gladly help you out.~
@58321 = ~I am pleased to meet you, my lady.~
@58322 = ~Hello, Afaaq. I am pleased to meet you, too.~
@58323 = ~It saddens me, however, to see you in a state like this.~
@58324 = ~Do not burden yourself with my own troubles. I am confident that it will not be a permanent state.~
@58325 = ~I am glad to see that <CHARNAME> was able to free you from your prison.~
@58326 = ~Yes, I am eternally thankful for <CHARNAME>'s deeds.~
@58327 = ~And as a token of my appreciation I will help <PRO_HIMHER> in turn to accomplish <PRO_HISHER> goal.~
@58328 = ~I'm certain that <CHARNAME> will find a way to release you from your unpleasant situation.~
@58329 = ~Well met, Afaaq. I'm looking forward to fruitful cooperation.~
@58330 = ~I greet you, druid. The pleasure is all mine.~
@58331 = ~Like a caged bird, dreaming to fly. Oh, how I long to see my home again.~
@58332 = ~Like a bird born anew. I may finally see my home again.~
@58333 = ~Well, well, well! Another lost bird has found his way into the fold.~
@58334 = ~How do you fare, my seasoned owl?~
@58335 = ~Ah yes, the marvelous planes... Once they capture your gaze, you can never stop thinking about them.~
@58336 = ~Don't forget that I'm also a turnip expert.~
@58337 = ~As my Uncle Scratchy always said, "Don't count your turnips before they are harvested". Even more so when Aunt Petunia was around. She was always sneaking into the garden to feast on the turnips, especially the young ones. You won't believe how often Uncle Scratchy had to plant new seedlings every month. And when she came around with--~
@58338 = ~Um, well, I can imagine your trouble with your relatives.~
@58339 = ~How true. As I was saying, when Aunt Petunia came around together with my great-aunt Apo Pettiwick--~
@58340 = ~As much as I appreciate your life story, but I doubt <CHARNAME> will be patient enough listening to you until the end of time.~
@58341 = ~Oh well, I'll tell you the rest later then.~
@58342 = ~Useful indeed. Without me you'd meet your end at the hand of the next second-rate mage crossing your path.~
@58343 = ~So, you are the plaything of <CHARNAME> for the moment? (I'm sure he'll be much more effective in my care.)~
@58344 = ~I am bound to the lamp which is in <CHARNAME>'s possession, not to <CHARNAME> <PRO_HIMHER>self.~
@58345 = ~Oh, I'm blushing... err, how DARE you make fun of my current state, <CHARNAME>?~
@58346 = ~But I will forgive your lack of manners, as I can see that you are going through an unusual situation yourself.~
@58347 = ~Hmpf, do you always have to emphasize my predicament, <CHARNAME>?~
@58348 = ~And you are <CHARNAME>'s new pet, I presume?~
@58349 = ~You assume correctly, ma'am. Your taunts are wasted on me, however.~
@58350 = ~Ne'er seen one of ye'r like before. What are ye for a beast?~
@58351 = ~I am neither beast nor creature. My kind is called the djinn, genies of the air.~
@58352 = ~A genie? Ye look more like a glorified punching bag to me. Care to show ye?~
@58353 = ~You may try if you wish. I do not care one way or another.~
@58354 = ~<CHARNAME>, did you drag yet another appendage into our party? He'd better be worth the price, or I'll take care of him myself.~
@58355 = ~There is no need for that. It is more likely that I can teach *you* a thing or two, if the need arises.~
@58356 = ~Whether I am worthy or not in your eyes has primarily been <CHARNAME>'s decision.~
