@60081 = ~This spell causes Afaaq to vanish from sight and be undetectable by normal vision or even infravision. Of course, the djinni is not magically silenced, and certain other conditions can render him detectable. Even allies cannot see Afaaq, unless these allies can normally see invisible things or employ magic to do so. The spell remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled, until he attacks any creature, or until 8 hours have passed.

Since Afaaq is born out of the chaotic forces of air, he can turn invisible anytime he wants.~
@60082 = ~Afaaq's close connection to the Elemental Plane of Air enables him to raise and control whirlwinds. His current condition allows him to surround himself with a small whirlwind that hurts and occasionally blinds any hostile creature in close vicinity. It also enables him to move at approximately double his normal movement rate. Once raised, the effect will stay active for about one turn.~
@60083 = ~Afaaq's close connection to the Elemental Plane of Air enables him to raise and control whirlwinds. After regaining his full power, he is able to create whirlwinds anywhere within sight. Each whirlwind causes damage and occasional blindness to any hostile creature in close vicinity.

Since whirlwinds are an extension of the djinni himself, he can observe his surroundings through the whirlwinds. Thus moving them out of sight doesn't make him lose control over them. The whirlwinds stay active for one turn at level 15 or less. Each additional character level adds one more round to the whirlwind's lifetime. If the djinni dies, loses his form or is affected by certain disabling effects even for a moment, the whirlwind will dissipate immediately.~
@60084 = ~This spell enables Afaaq to move at about double his normal movement rate. He also gains a -2 initiative bonus, and receives an extra attack per round. The effect will stay active for five turns.

Since Afaaq is born out of the chaotic forces of air, he can haste himself anytime he wants.~
@60085 = ~The Air Shield grants Afaaq immunity to electricity damage, as well as high resistances to magical or missile damage. It also reduces physical melee damage somewhat. Any opponent that hits Afaaq in close combat while the effect is active suffers 2d8 points of electrical damage and 1d8 points of crushing and slashing damage. The shield will stay active for two turns.~
@60086 = ~This spell allows Afaaq to take control over any creature of aerial origin within his sight, such as Air Elementals, Aerial Servants or Invisible Stalkers. If the aerial creature fails its save vs. spell at a -4 penalty, it will stay under Afaaq's control for one turn before turning hostile.~
